-- Mechel, Sberbank, Tatneft Shares May Move: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2010-12-14T21:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/mechel-sberbank-tatneft-russian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index  added 0.2 percent to 1,666.28. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 0.6 percent to 1,745.80, its
highest closing level since August 2008.       OAO Mechel  (MTLR RX), Russia’s largest miner of steelmaking
coal, expects prices to rise about 30 percent next year from
average rates in 2010, according to  Alexander Proskurin, a
commercial director at the company. Michel rose 1.8 percent to
855.18 rubles.  OAO Sberbank  (SBER03 RX) will report its sales and revenue
figures for eleven months through November in accordance with
Russian accounting standards. Russia’s biggest lender slipped
0.1 percent to 107.30 rubles.  OAO Tatneft  (TATN3 RX) is scheduled to report third-quarter
earnings. The biggest oil producer in Russia’s Tatarstan region
was little changed, gaining less than 0.1 percent to 147.37
rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
